{"step_index":6252,"source":"MODEL","type":"PLANNER_RESPONSE","status":"DONE","created_at":"2026-06-13T04:00:15Z","thinking":"**Prioritizing Tool Specificity**\n\nI'm focusing intently on tool specificity. I've internalized the instruction to avoid `cat` for file creation/appending at all costs. I'm also now actively favoring `grep_search` over in-line `grep` usage. It’s ingrained: no `ls` unless utterly unavoidable! This mindset shift promises cleaner, more efficient scripting.\n\n\n**Refining Tool Choice Logic**\n\nI'm now deeply engaged in refining my tool selection logic. I'm expanding my internal \"tool checklist\" before execution, actively listing all relevant tools to ensure I choose the most specific and appropriate option. I'm focusing on \"cat\" for viewing, \"grep\" for finding, \"sed\" for replacing, and integrating these into a deliberate workflow. My current task is replacing the component content with a carefully written new one.\n\n\n**Analyzing Data Structure and States**\n\nI'm now analyzing the data structures and component states. I see the use of `useState` for managing menu items, orders, wallets, toast messages, and tab selections. I notice the implementation of local storage for persistence. I am focused on the \"newItem\" state which includes name, price, category, icon, and quantity. I am also assessing scanning and cart states. I'm noting the clear separation of concerns in the state management.\n\n\n**Examining State Synchronization**\n\nI'm now carefully examining the state synchronization mechanisms. The code uses `useEffect` hooks for local storage updates and syncing data across tabs and browser sessions. I'm focusing on the `localStorage` interactions, particularly how the `menu`, `orders`, and `wallets` states are persisted and retrieved. The event listeners for 'storage' and 'moo-sync' are being studied to see how they enable real-time updates. I see an interval for synchronization, and I'm assessing its frequency and the implications for data consistency. Finally, I'm analyzing the data structures within each state variable, like the `cart`, `customAmount`, and the array of objects that represent the items in the menu.\n\n\n**Evaluating Scanner Integration**\n\nI'm now evaluating the scanner integration. I'm focusing on the `Html5QrcodeScanner` setup and the event handling within `useEffect`. I'm paying close attention to the parsing of the QR code data and how it updates the component state. The `JSON.parse` within the scanner's callback is critical, especially the error handling, and the updates to `scannedStudent`, `cart`, `customAmount`, and toast messages. I'm also examining how the scanner is cleared to optimize the resources used by the device, as well as the scanner's initialization and the return cleanup function.\n\n\n**Assessing State Transitions**\n\nI'm now carefully examining the state transitions and function implementations related to inventory management, particularly how items are added. I am assessing `handleAddItem`, focusing on its event handling, form validation (specifically for the item's name), and integration with the `menu` state. The logic to handle potential errors in camera access, and toast messages is being closely assessed to ensure a smooth user experience. I am now considering the use of `useMemo` for performance improvements.\n\n\n**Analyzing Item Updates**\n\nI'm now analyzing the functions related to item management within the application's menu. I'm focusing on `handleAddItem`, which validates input before creating new items with unique IDs based on timestamps. I also see how the quantity can be updated using `updateQuantity`. The `deleteItem` functionality utilizes `window.confirm`. I also see how `addToCart` handles item additions, accounting for quantity and availability.\n\n\n**Reviewing Cart Operations**\n\nI'm now carefully reviewing the cart operations. I'm focusing on `addToCart`, which manages quantity checks and updates, ensuring available stock isn't exceeded, and handles adding new or existing items to the cart. I see how `removeFromCart` removes items, and how `cartTotal` calculates the overall amount. I'm analyzing the `handleCheckout` function, which determines the amount to deduct based on cart contents or custom amounts, crafting a detailed summary of the purchase.\n\n\n**Evaluating Wallet Interactions**\n\nI'm now carefully evaluating wallet interactions within the checkout flow. I'm focusing on the `handleCheckout` function, specifically how it deducts balances and updates vault storage. I'm noting the balance check and the feedback given to the user. I'm analyzing the transaction logging, including the data structure for new entries, which incorporates student ID, name, transaction amount, type, and date. The balance update logic is clear, and the vault update logic seems safe.\n\n\n**Processing Order and Inventory**\n\nI'm now processing order creation and subsequent menu inventory updates. I see the creation of new orders and the corresponding updating of menu quantities after processing the cart. The code generates a new order object with details like student name, items, and total. Then, the orders are updated in local storage and inventory adjusted using `setMenu` if needed. I see an event for storage to signal updates. I'm focusing on the data structure and how the state is modified and persisted.\n\n\n**Analyzing Checkout Completion**\n\nI'm now analyzing the completion of the checkout process, specifically focusing on the clearing of student information and cart contents. The code resets `scannedStudent` to null, clears the `cart` array, and resets the `customAmount` string after a successful checkout. I am assessing the direct impact of these resets. The toast message also provides feedback to the user on the outcome of the action. Finally, I'm focusing on the component state updates.\n\n\n**Evaluating Header Component**\n\nI'm now carefully evaluating the `<header>` component, focusing on its structure and styling. I see the main container using `flex` and `justify-between` for layout. I'm focusing on the component's sections, including the logo/title and the logout button. The colors and typography are being assessed for overall visual consistency and clarity. I'm also examining the responsiveness, especially on smaller screens.\n\n\n**Assessing Stats Display**\n\nI'm now carefully assessing the sales and order statistics display within the application. I see the utilization of `TrendingUp` and `Receipt` icons to visually represent sales and order counts. I am focusing on the structure using `flex` for arrangement and the `text` classes for styling, specifically the color and size of the text elements. The formatting of the numerical values, including the use of Arabic characters, is also important. The design emphasizes clarity and readability, which is key. The stats' data source is not yet clear.\n\n\n**Analyzing Inventory Low Stock**\n\nI'm now carefully analyzing the display for low inventory. I see a container with a ring effect based on `lowStock` quantity, which is a great indicator. I'm focusing on the component structure, including the `AlertTriangle` icon and the styling of the text elements. The formatting of the numerical data within the component, specifically the use of Arabic characters for the number, and the units. The code logic for updating the count is not yet clear.\n\n\n**Reviewing Tabbed Navigation**\n\nI'm now reviewing the tabbed navigation component. I'm focusing on the component's structure, the usage of the `map` function to create the buttons, and the conditional styling based on the `activeTab` state. I am assessing the tab content rendering using `<AnimatePresence>` for transitions, and I'm analyzing the styling, particularly the use of `flex`, `items-center`, `gap-2`, and rounded corners. I'm now noting the tab IDs: 'pos', 'inventory', and 'orders'.\n\n\n**Evaluating Scanner Start**\n\nI'm now carefully evaluating the initial scanner activation flow. I see the `startScanning` function, crucial to initiating the QR code scanning process. I am focusing on how the scanner is initialized. The handling of user permissions and the interaction with the HTML5 QR code library are key. I'm focusing on the condition where `scannedStudent` is not null to ensure that the scanner doesn't activate. I am assessing how the `isScanning` state is updated, to control the scanner's start and stop state, and prevent overlapping events.\n\n\n**Evaluating Scanner Deactivation**\n\nI'm now carefully evaluating the scanner deactivation process. I'm focusing on the `setIsScanning(false)` call and its interaction with the `<button>` component to stop scanning. I see how the `Html5QrcodeScanner` instance is being cleaned up and the scanner is terminated. I'm focusing on the component state updates as well as the transition when the scan is canceled. I'm also examining the conditional rendering of the scanner interface.\n\n\n**Analyzing Student Display**\n\nI'm now carefully analyzing the display of student information within the application. I see the container's styling, with a gradient background, rounded corners, and shadow, as well as the use of the `X` icon. The logic to clear student data is being examined. I'm focusing on the component structure. I'm noting the text elements, specifically the student's name and ID, and their styling, including font size and weight, and the use of Arabic characters. I'm assessing how user feedback is presented.\n\n\n**Evaluating Wallet Display**\n\nI'm now carefully evaluating the wallet display component and its interactions. I see a blurred backdrop with rounded corners, and a border. I'm focusing on the presentation of the balance, including the text colors and size, as well as the display format for the currency, which is shown in Arabic characters. The structure uses flex for alignment. I'm noting the integration of the Wallet icon. I am focusing on the balance display for clarity and user feedback.\n\n\n**Assessing Cart Display**\n\nI'm now carefully assessing the cart display within the application, and the way items can be added to the cart. I see several distinct sections. I'm focusing on the overall layout. The logic for filtering items based on inventory, and displaying \"No items\" is important. The addition of items to the cart, including the styling, are important, and the overall style and accessibility is key. I'm noting the custom scrolling element for mobile and the styling of the items displayed.\n\n\n**Refining Display Logic**\n\nI'm now refining the display logic for menu items and the cart content. I'm focusing on the component's conditional rendering based on inventory levels, and how the \"No items\" message is shown. I'm assessing the button styles, including their responsiveness and hover states, especially for the menu item components. I see the use of Arabic characters for currency and the use of flex for layout within the components. I'm also ensuring all styles are consistent.\n\n\n**Analyzing Cart Item Formatting**\n\nI'm now analyzing the formatting of cart items. I see the use of flexbox for layout, with the icon, item details, and removal button arranged neatly. I'm focusing on text styling, including sizes, colors, and the Arabic currency display. The removal button's hover state is also key for interactivity. The quantity display and total price calculation are also being assessed.\n\n\n**Evaluating Custom Amount Input**\n\nI'm now carefully evaluating the custom amount input functionality within the checkout flow. I'm focusing on the input's conditional state, and how it's disabled if the cart has content. I see the placeholder text that updates accordingly. The number input is set, and the use of the `step` attribute and the validation on input. The interaction of the `customAmount` state is also key.\n\n\n\n**Evaluating Checkout Buttons**\n\nI'm now carefully evaluating the checkout button. I am focusing on the visual cues provided, like text color, background, and disabled state appearance. The functionality associated with scanning the student, cart contents, and custom amount input are important factors. The use of a circular check icon is assessed for clarity. The logic to handle checkout is clear. The Arabic text should be correct and the alignment of elements is assessed.\n\n\n\n**Assessing Item Addition**\n\nI'm now carefully assessing the item addition form and its associated logic. The form utilizes emojis for item icons and allows the user to input the item's name. I see the handling of the form submission. I'm focusing on the component's styling and form inputs and their validation. The integration of the selected emoji into the `newItem` state is also key. The validation of the form is also being reviewed to ensure an ideal flow.\n\n\n**Evaluating Item Price Input**\n\nI am now carefully evaluating the item price input field within the form. I'm focusing on the input's attributes, particularly `type=\"number\"`, `min=\"0.1\"`, and `step=\"0.1\"`. The placeholder text \"0.0\" is being examined, as is how the Arabic characters and numerical values render. I'm assessing the validation logic and error handling. The overall visual appearance of the input field is also assessed.\n\n\n**Evaluating Item Quantity Input**\n\nI'm now carefully evaluating the quantity input field within the item form, focusing on its attributes, like `type=\"number\"`, `min=\"1\"`, and its use of Arabic characters. I'm also examining how the input updates the `newItem` state and the placeholder text. The overall visual appearance, including the border style and the focus state, is being assessed for consistency.\n\n\n**Analyzing Menu Component Rendering**\n\nI'm now carefully analyzing the menu component's rendering logic. I'm focusing on the conditional rendering of the menu grid or \"no items\" message based on the `menu.length` state. The layout utilizes `flex`, `grid`, and `gap` to arrange the content. I'm noting the text styling, and the use of Arabic text. I am also assessing how menu items are shown.\n\n\n**Assessing Menu Item Deletion**\n\nI'm focusing now on menu item deletion within the component. The `deleteItem` function is essential. I see that there is a deletion button and the functionality that is tied into the button. The event handling and the confirmation prompt, using `window.confirm`, are crucial. I'm noting the immediate visual update within the `menu` state. The styling of the deletion button, including the hover effects and transitions, is important for a smooth user experience.\n\n\n**Assessing Component Styling**\n\nI am now assessing the styling of the menu item and its parts. I see the use of `flex` for layout with a description below. I see the `category` text, `price` text, and the quantity controls. I am noting the use of colors and fonts for clarity. The layout of the price and currency is being assessed. I am focusing on the visual hierarchy, especially the use of bolding and colors to emphasize key information for the user.\n\n\n**Refining Component Interactions**\n\nI'm now carefully examining the interactions within the menu and quantity updates for individual items. I see the addition and subtraction, and I'm focused on their interaction with the `updateQuantity` function and how it modifies the `menu` state directly, as well as the button styles. I'm focusing on quantity changes. I am noting the use of Arabic text in the content. I am now assessing the component's interactive elements.\n\n\n**Reviewing Order Display**\n\nI'm now carefully reviewing the order display within the application, and am focusing on the order listing section. I see conditional rendering. I see Arabic text and the layout. I am noting the use of 'Receipt' icon. I am focusing on the structure of individual order items and how they are displayed. I'm focusing on their display, including the use of an icon and styling for 'direct sell' orders. The responsive design for different screen sizes is also important.\n\n\n**Evaluating Order Component Details**\n\nI'm now carefully evaluating the order component details display, especially the individual order item details. I'm focusing on the integration of Arabic text within the component, and I am assessing the use of different elements. I'm noting the student's name, ID, and the order date and time. I see the use of `Clock` icons and other elements for an attractive UI. I'm focusing on readability and the overall layout.\n\n\n**Refining Cart Logic**\n\nI'm now refining the `addToCart` function to incorporate stock level checks. I'm focusing on validating the potential new quantity against the existing `quantity` in stock for each item before adding to the cart. This ensures inventory isn't exceeded, preventing over-selling. I am also planning on implementing better error messages for clarity.\n\n\n","tool_calls":[{"name":"write_to_file","args":{"ArtifactMetadata":{"RequestFeedback":false,"Summary":"استبدال كود البوابة بالكامل لتطبيق التصميم الجديد والميزات المتكاملة وإزالة البيانات الوهمية.","UserFacing":false},"CodeContent":"import React, { useState, useEffect, useMemo } from 'react';\nimport { motion, AnimatePresence } from 'framer-motion';\nimport {\n  Store, Plus, Save, Trash2, CheckCircle2, BellRing, AlertTriangle,\n  Receipt, QrCode, X, CreditCard, LayoutGrid, Package, ChevronRight,\n  ShoppingCart, Search, Tag, Wallet, TrendingUp, Clock, Scan\n} from 'lucide-react';\nimport { Html5QrcodeScanner } from 'html5-qrcode';\nimport PropTypes from 'prop-types';\n\nconst CATEGORIES = ['ساندوتشات', 'مشروبات', 'تسالي', 'معجنات', 'أخرى'];\nconst EMOJIS = ['🥪', '🍔', '🍕', '🌭', '🍟', '🧃', '🥤', '☕', '🥐', '🥯', '🍩', '🍫', '🍬', '🍿', '🍱', '🥗', '🍎'];\n\nconst CafeteriaAdminDashboard = ({ onLogout }) => {\n  // 1. STATE (NO FAKE DATA)\n  const [menu, setMenu] = useState(() => JSON.parse(localStorage.getItem('moo_cafeteria_menu')) || []);\n  const [orders, setOrders] = useState(() => JSON.parse(localStorage.getItem('moo_cafeteria_orders')) || []);\n  const [wallets, setWallets] = useState(() => JSON.parse(localStorage.getItem('moo_wallets')) || {});\n  \n  const [successToast, setSuccessToast] = useState('');\n  const [activeTab, setActiveTab] = useState('pos'); // pos, inventory, orders\n\n  // Form states\n  const [newItem, setNewItem] = useState({ name: '', price: '', category: 'ساندوتشات', icon: '🥪', quantity: '' });\n  \n  // Scanner states\n  const [isScanning, setIsScanning] = useState(false);\n  const [scannedStudent, setScannedStudent] = useState(null);\n  \n  // POS states\n  const [cart, setCart] = useState([]); // Array of { ...menuItem, cartQty }\n  const [customAmount, setCustomAmount] = useState('');\n\n  // 2. LIFECYCLE & SYNC\n  useEffect(() => {\n    localStorage.setItem('moo_cafeteria_menu', JSON.stringify(menu));\n    window.dispatchEvent(new Event('storage'));\n  }, [menu]);\n\n  useEffect(() => {\n    const handleSync = () => {\n      setOrders(JSON.parse(localStorage.getItem('moo_cafeteria_orders')) || []);\n      setWallets(JSON.parse(localStorage.getItem('moo_wallets')) || {});\n      setMenu(JSON.parse(localStorage.getItem('moo_cafeteria_menu')) || []);\n    };\n    window.addEventListener('storage', handleSync);\n    window.addEventListener('moo-sync', handleSync);\n    const interval = setInterval(handleSync, 3000);\n    return () => {\n      window.removeEventListener('storage', handleSync);\n      window.removeEventListener('moo-sync', handleSync);\n      clearInterval(interval);\n    };\n  }, []);\n\n  // 3. SCANNER LOGIC\n  useEffect(() => {\n    let scanner;\n    if (isScanning) {\n      const timer = setTimeout(() => {\n        try {\n          scanner = new Html5QrcodeScanner('reader', { \n            qrbox: { width: 250, height: 250 }, \n            fps: 10,\n            aspectRatio: 1.0\n          }, false);\n          scanner.render((text) => {\n            try {\n              const data = JSON.parse(text);\n              if (data && data.id) {\n                scanner.clear();\n                setIsScanning(false);\n                setScannedStudent(data);\n                setCart([]);\n                setCustomAmount('');\n                showToast('✅ تم قراءة كود الطالب بنجاح');\n              }\n            } catch (e) {\n              // ignore invalid JSON\n            }\n          }, () => { /* ignore scan errors */ });\n        } catch (e) {\n          console.error(\"Scanner failed:\", e);\n        }\n      }, 100);\n\n      return () => {\n        clearTimeout(timer);\n        if (scanner) {\n          scanner.clear().catch(() => {});\n        }\n      };\n    }\n  }, [isScanning]);\n\n  const startScanning = async () => {\n    try {\n      await navigator.mediaDevices.getUserMedia({ video: true });\n      setIsScanning(true);\n    } catch (err) {\n      alert('❌ فشل الوصول للكاميرا. يرجى السماح باستخدام الكاميرا.');\n    }\n  };\n\n  // 4. HELPERS\n  const showToast = (msg) => {\n    setSuccessToast(msg);\n    setTimeout(() => setSuccessToast(''), 3000);\n  };\n\n  const isToday = (dateStr) => {\n    if (!dateStr) return false;\n    const d = new Date(dateStr);\n    const t = new Date();\n    return d.getDate() === t.getDate() && d.getMonth() === t.getMonth() && d.getFullYear() === t.getFullYear();\n  };\n\n  // 5. STATS CALCULATION\n  const stats = useMemo(() => {\n    const todayOrders = orders.filter(o => isToday(o.date));\n    const todaySales = todayOrders.reduce((sum, o) => sum + (Number(o.total) || 0), 0);\n    const lowStock = menu.filter(m => m.quantity < 5);\n    return { ordersCount: todayOrders.length, sales: todaySales, lowStock: lowStock.length };\n  }, [orders, menu]);\n\n  // 6. INVENTORY MANAGEMENT\n  const handleAddItem = (e) => {\n    e.preventDefault();\n    if (!newItem.name.trim() || !newItem.price || !newItem.quantity) return;\n    const item = {\n      ...newItem,\n      id: Date.now(),\n      price: parseFloat(newItem.price),\n      quantity: parseInt(newItem.quantity, 10)\n    };\n    setMenu([item, ...menu]);\n    setNewItem({ name: '', price: '', category: 'ساندوتشات', icon: '🥪', quantity: '' });\n    showToast('تمت إضافة الصنف بنجاح');\n  };\n\n  const updateQuantity = (id, delta) => {\n    setMenu(menu.map(m => {\n      if (m.id === id) {\n        const nq = m.quantity + delta;\n        return { ...m, quantity: nq < 0 ? 0 : nq };\n      }\n      return m;\n    }));\n  };\n\n  const deleteItem = (id) => {\n    if (window.confirm('هل أنت متأكد من حذف هذا الصنف؟')) {\n      setMenu(menu.filter(m => m.id !== id));\n    }\n  };\n\n  // 7. POINT OF SALE (POS) LOGIC\n  const addToCart = (item) => {\n    if (item.quantity <= 0) return showToast('❌ عذراً، هذا الصنف غير متوفر حالياً');\n    \n    const existing = cart.find(c => c.id === item.id);\n    if (existing) {\n      if (existing.cartQty >= item.quantity) return showToast('❌ تم تجاوز الكمية المتاحة');\n      setCart(cart.map(c => c.id === item.id ? { ...c, cartQty: c.cartQty + 1 } : c));\n    } else {\n      setCart([...cart, { ...item, cartQty: 1 }]);\n    }\n    setCustomAmount(''); // clear custom amount if using cart\n  };\n\n  const removeFromCart = (id) => {\n    setCart(cart.filter(c => c.id !== id));\n  };\n\n  const cartTotal = cart.reduce((sum, item) => sum + (item.price * item.cartQty), 0);\n  \n  const handleCheckout = () => {\n    if (!scannedStudent) return;\n    \n    let totalToDeduct = 0;\n    let itemsString = '';\n    \n    if (cart.length > 0) {\n      totalToDeduct = cartTotal;\n      itemsString = cart.map(c => `${c.name} (${c.cartQty})`).join(' + ');\n    } else if (customAmount && parseFloat(customAmount) > 0) {\n      totalToDeduct = parseFloat(customAmount);\n      itemsString = 'مشتريات مباشرة متنوعة';\n    } else {\n      return showToast('❌ يرجى اختيار أصناف أو إدخال مبلغ صحيح');\n    }\n\n    const currentBalance = wallets[scannedStudent.id] || 0;\n    if (currentBalance < totalToDeduct) {\n      return showToast('❌ رصيد الطالب لا يكفي لإتمام العملية!');\n    }\n\n    // 1. Deduct wallet\n    const updatedWallets = { ...wallets, [scannedStudent.id]: currentBalance - totalToDeduct };\n    setWallets(updatedWallets);\n    localStorage.setItem('moo_wallets', JSON.stringify(updatedWallets));\n\n    // 2. Add to vault\n    const currentVault = parseFloat(localStorage.getItem('moo_school_vault')) || 0;\n    localStorage.setItem('moo_school_vault', (currentVault + totalToDeduct).toString());\n\n    // 3. Log transaction\n    const txLog = JSON.parse(localStorage.getItem('moo_wallet_transactions')) || [];\n    const newTx = {\n      id: Date.now(),\n      studentId: scannedStudent.id,\n      studentName: scannedStudent.name,\n      amount: totalToDeduct,\n      type: 'subtract',\n      date: new Date().toISOString()\n    };\n    localStorage.setItem('moo_wallet_transactions', JSON.stringify([newTx, ...txLog].slice(0, 50)));\n\n    // 4. Create Order\n    const newOrder = {\n      id: Date.now(),\n      studentName: scannedStudent.name,\n      studentId: scannedStudent.id,\n      items: itemsString,\n      total: totalToDeduct,\n      date: new Date().toISOString(),\n      status: 'completed',\n      source: 'pos' // indicates point of sale direct\n    };\n    const updatedOrders = [newOrder, ...orders].slice(0, 100);\n    setOrders(updatedOrders);\n    localStorage.setItem('moo_cafeteria_orders', JSON.stringify(updatedOrders));\n\n    // 5. Update Menu inventory if cart was used\n    if (cart.length > 0) {\n      let updatedMenu = [...menu];\n      cart.forEach(cItem => {\n        updatedMenu = updatedMenu.map(m => m.id === cItem.id ? { ...m, quantity: m.quantity - cItem.cartQty } : m);\n      });\n      setMenu(updatedMenu);\n    }\n\n    window.dispatchEvent(new Event('storage'));\n    \n    showToast(`✅ تم إتمام العملية بنجاح! خصم ${totalToDeduct} ر.س`);\n    setScannedStudent(null);\n    setCart([]);\n    setCustomAmount('');\n  };\n\n  // RENDER HELPERS\n  const balance = scannedStudent ? (wallets[scannedStudent.id] || 0) : 0;\n\n  return (\n    <div className=\"min-h-screen bg-slate-50 font-sans\" dir=\"rtl\">\n      {/* TOAST */}\n      <AnimatePresence>\n        {successToast && (\n          <motion.div initial={{ opacity: 0, y: -20 }} animate={{ opacity: 1, y: 0 }} exit={{ opacity: 0, y: -20 }}\n            className=\"fixed top-6 left-1/2 -translate-x-1/2 z-[100] bg-emerald-600 text-white px-6 py-3 rounded-2xl shadow-xl flex items-center gap-3 font-bold text-sm\">\n            <CheckCircle2 size={18} />\n            {successToast}\n          </motion.div>\n        )}\n      </AnimatePresence>\n\n      {/* HEADER */}\n      <header className=\"bg-white/90 backdrop-blur-md border-b border-slate-100 sticky top-0 z-50 shadow-sm\">\n        <div className=\"max-w-7xl mx-auto px-6 h-20 flex items-center justify-between\">\n          <div className=\"flex items-center gap-4\">\n            <div className=\"w-12 h-12 bg-orange-100 rounded-2xl flex items-center justify-center text-orange-600 shadow-inner\">\n              <Store size={24} />\n            </div>\n            <div>\n              <h1 className=\"text-xl font-black text-slate-800\">إدارة المقصف الذكي</h1>\n              <p className=\"text-xs font-bold text-slate-400\">نظام المبيعات والجرد المباشر</p>\n            </div>\n          </div>\n          <button onClick={onLogout} className=\"px-5 py-2.5 bg-rose-50 text-rose-600 hover:bg-rose-100 rounded-xl font-bold text-sm transition-colors flex items-center gap-2\">\n            تسجيل الخروج\n          </button>\n        </div>\n      </header>\n\n      <main className=\"max-w-7xl mx-auto px-6 py-8\">\n        \n        {/* STATS OVERVIEW */}\n        <div className=\"grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-3 gap-6 mb-8\">\n          <div className=\"bg-white rounded-3xl p-6 border border-slate-100 shadow-sm flex items-center gap-5\">\n            <div className=\"w-14 h-14 rounded-2xl bg-emerald-50 text-emerald-600 flex items-center justify-center shrink-0\">\n              <TrendingUp size={24} />\n            </div>\n            <div>\n              <p className=\"text-sm font-bold text-slate-400\">مبيعات اليوم</p>\n              <p className=\"text-2xl font-black text-slate-800\">{stats.sales} <span className=\"text-sm text-slate-400 font-bold\">ر.س</span></p>\n            </div>\n          </div>\n          \n          <div className=\"bg-white rounded-3xl p-6 border border-slate-100 shadow-sm flex items-center gap-5\">\n            <div className=\"w-14 h-14 rounded-2xl bg-blue-50 text-blue-600 flex items-center justify-center shrink-0\">\n              <Receipt size={24} />\n            </div>\n            <div>\n              <p className=\"text-sm font-bold text-slate-400\">الطلبات اليوم</p>\n              <p className=\"text-2xl font-black text-slate-800\">{stats.ordersCount} <span className=\"text-sm text-slate-400 font-bold\">طلب</span></p>\n            </div>\n          </div>\n\n          <div className={`bg-white rounded-3xl p-6 border border-slate-100 shadow-sm flex items-center gap-5 ${stats.lowStock > 0 ? 'ring-2 ring-rose-400 ring-offset-2' : ''}`}>\n            <div className={`w-14 h-14 rounded-2xl flex items-center justify-center shrink-0 ${stats.lowStock > 0 ? 'bg-rose-100 text-rose-600' : 'bg-slate-50 text-slate-400'}`}>\n              <AlertTriangle size={24} />\n            </div>\n            <div>\n              <p className=\"text-sm font-bold text-slate-400\">نواقص المخزون</p>\n              <p className=\"text-2xl font-black text-slate-800\">{stats.lowStock} <span className=\"text-sm text-slate-400 font-bold\">صنف</span></p>\n            </div>\n          </div>\n        </div>\n\n        {/* TABS NAVIGATION */}\n        <div className=\"flex gap-2 p-1.5 bg-white border border-slate-100 rounded-2xl mb-8 w-fit shadow-sm overflow-x-auto max-w-full\">\n          {[\n            { id: 'pos', icon: QrCode, label: 'البيع المباشر' },\n            { id: 'inventory', icon: Package, label: 'المخزون والقائمة' },\n            { id: 'orders', icon: BellRing, label: 'الطلبات الحية' }\n          ].map(t => (\n            <button key={t.id} onClick={() => setActiveTab(t.id)}\n              className={`flex items-center gap-2 px-6 py-3 rounded-xl font-bold text-sm transition-all whitespace-nowrap ${\n                activeTab === t.id ? 'bg-orange-500 text-white shadow-md shadow-orange-500/20' : 'text-slate-500 hover:bg-slate-50'\n              }`}>\n              <t.icon size={18} /> {t.label}\n            </button>\n          ))}\n        </div>\n\n        {/* CONTENT */}\n        <AnimatePresence mode=\"wait\">\n          \n          {/* TAB 1: POINT OF SALE */}\n          {activeTab === 'pos' && (\n            <motion.div key=\"pos\" initial={{ opacity: 0, y: 10 }} animate={{ opacity: 1, y: 0 }} exit={{ opacity: 0 }} className=\"grid grid-cols-1 lg:grid-cols-12 gap-6\">\n              \n              {/* SCANNER SIDE */}\n              <div className=\"lg:col-span-5 space-y-6\">\n                <div className=\"bg-white rounded-[2rem] p-6 shadow-sm border border-slate-100 relative overflow-hidden\">\n                  <div className=\"absolute top-0 right-0 w-32 h-32 bg-orange-50 rounded-bl-full -z-0 opacity-50\" />\n                  <h2 className=\"text-lg font-black text-slate-800 mb-6 flex items-center gap-2 relative z-10\">\n                    <Scan size={20} className=\"text-orange-500\" />\n                    ماسح البطاقات (QR)\n                  </h2>\n                  \n                  {!isScanning && !scannedStudent && (\n                    <div className=\"text-center py-10 relative z-10\">\n                      <div className=\"w-24 h-24 bg-orange-100 rounded-full flex items-center justify-center text-orange-500 mx-auto mb-6 shadow-inner\">\n                        <QrCode size={40} />\n                      </div>\n                      <p className=\"text-slate-500 font-bold text-sm mb-6\">امسح كود الطالب للبدء بعملية البيع</p>\n                      <button onClick={startScanning} className=\"w-full bg-slate-900 text-white py-4 rounded-2xl font-black shadow-xl shadow-slate-900/20 hover:scale-[1.02] transition-transform flex items-center justify-center gap-2\">\n                        <Scan size={18} /> تشغيل الكاميرا\n                      </button>\n                    </div>\n                  )}\n\n                  {isScanning && (\n                    <div className=\"relative z-10\">\n                      <div className=\"bg-slate-900 rounded-3xl overflow-hidden shadow-2xl p-2 mb-4 border-4 border-slate-800\">\n                        <div id=\"reader\" className=\"w-full rounded-2xl overflow-hidden bg-black [&>div]:border-none [&>div>video]:rounded-xl\"></div>\n                      </div>\n                      <button onClick={() => setIsScanning(false)} className=\"w-full bg-rose-50 text-rose-600 py-3 rounded-xl font-bold hover:bg-rose-100 transition-colors\">\n                        إغلاق الكاميرا\n                      </button>\n                    </div>\n                  )}\n\n                  {scannedStudent && (\n                    <div className=\"relative z-10 bg-gradient-to-br from-orange-500 to-orange-600 rounded-3xl p-6 text-white shadow-xl shadow-orange-500/20\">\n                      <div className=\"flex justify-between items-start mb-6\">\n                        <div className=\"w-14 h-14 bg-white/20 backdrop-blur-sm rounded-2xl flex items-center justify-center text-2xl border border-white/30 shadow-inner\">\n                          👤\n                        </div>\n                        <button onClick={() => { setScannedStudent(null); setCart([]); setCustomAmount(''); }} className=\"bg-white/20 hover:bg-white/30 p-2 rounded-xl transition-colors\">\n                          <X size={16} />\n                        </button>\n                      </div>\n                      <p className=\"text-orange-100 text-xs font-bold mb-1\">بيانات الطالب</p>\n                      <h3 className=\"text-xl font-black mb-1\">{scannedStudent.name}</h3>\n                      <p className=\"text-orange-200 text-xs font-mono mb-6 opacity-80\">{scannedStudent.id}</p>\n                      \n                      <div className=\"bg-white/10 backdrop-blur-md rounded-2xl p-4 border border-white/20\">\n                        <p className=\"text-orange-100 text-xs font-bold mb-1 flex items-center gap-1\"><Wallet size={12}/> الرصيد المتاح</p>\n                        <p className=\"text-3xl font-black\">{balance.toFixed(2)} <span className=\"text-sm\">ر.س</span></p>\n                      </div>\n                    </div>\n                  )}\n                </div>\n              </div>\n\n              {/* CART & POS SIDE */}\n              <div className={`lg:col-span-7 transition-opacity duration-300 ${!scannedStudent ? 'opacity-40 pointer-events-none grayscale' : ''}`}>\n                <div className=\"bg-white rounded-[2rem] p-6 shadow-sm border border-slate-100 h-full flex flex-col\">\n                  \n                  <div className=\"flex items-center justify-between mb-6\">\n                    <h2 className=\"text-lg font-black text-slate-800 flex items-center gap-2\">\n                      <ShoppingCart size={20} className=\"text-orange-500\" /> سلة الشراء السريعة\n                    </h2>\n                    <div className=\"bg-orange-50 text-orange-600 px-3 py-1 rounded-lg text-xs font-bold\">\n                      الإجمالي: {(cartTotal || parseFloat(customAmount || 0)).toFixed(2)} ر.س\n                    </div>\n                  </div>\n\n                  {/* Mode 1: Cart from Menu */}\n                  <div className=\"flex-1 min-h-[250px]\">\n                    <div className=\"mb-4\">\n                      <p className=\"text-xs font-bold text-slate-400 mb-3\">اختر من القائمة:</p>\n                      <div className=\"flex gap-2 overflow-x-auto pb-2 custom-scrollbar\">\n                        {menu.filter(m => m.quantity > 0).length === 0 ? (\n                          <p className=\"text-sm text-slate-400 font-bold p-4 bg-slate-50 rounded-xl w-full text-center border border-dashed border-slate-200\">لا يوجد أصناف متاحة في المخزون</p>\n                        ) : (\n                          menu.filter(m => m.quantity > 0).map(item => (\n                            <button key={item.id} onClick={() => addToCart(item)}\n                              className=\"shrink-0 bg-slate-50 hover:bg-orange-50 border border-slate-100 hover:border-orange-200 rounded-2xl p-3 flex flex-col items-center gap-2 transition-all group w-24\">\n                              <span className=\"text-3xl group-hover:scale-110 transition-transform\">{item.icon}</span>\n                              <p className=\"text-[10px] font-bold text-slate-600 text-center truncate w-full\">{item.name}</p>\n                              <p className=\"text-xs font-black text-orange-500\">{item.price} ر.س</p>\n                            </button>\n                          ))\n                        )}\n                      </div>\n                    </div>\n\n                    {cart.length > 0 && (\n                      <div className=\"bg-slate-50 rounded-2xl border border-slate-100 p-4 space-y-2 max-h-48 overflow-y-auto\">\n                        {cart.map(c => (\n                          <div key={c.id} className=\"flex justify-between items-center bg-white p-3 rounded-xl shadow-sm border border-slate-100\">\n                            <div className=\"flex items-center gap-3\">\n                              <span className=\"text-xl\">{c.icon}</span>\n                              <div>\n                                <p className=\"text-sm font-bold text-slate-800\">{c.name}</p>\n                                <p className=\"text-xs text-orange-500 font-bold\">{c.price} ر.س × {c.cartQty}</p>\n                              </div>\n                            </div>\n                            <div className=\"flex items-center gap-4\">\n                              <p className=\"font-black text-slate-800\">{(c.price * c.cartQty).toFixed(2)}</p>\n                              <button onClick={() => removeFromCart(c.id)} className=\"w-8 h-8 flex items-center justify-center rounded-lg bg-rose-50 text-rose-500 hover:bg-rose-500 hover:text-white transition-colors\">\n                                <Trash2 size={14} />\n                              </button>\n                            </div>\n                          </div>\n                        ))}\n                      </div>\n                    )}\n                  </div>\n\n                  {/* Mode 2: Custom Amount OR Checkout */}\n                  <div className=\"mt-6 pt-6 border-t border-slate-100\">\n                    <p className=\"text-xs font-bold text-slate-400 mb-3\">أو إدخال مبلغ مخصص (بدون تحديد أصناف):</p>\n                    <div className=\"flex gap-4\">\n                      <div className=\"flex-1 relative\">\n                        <input type=\"number\" min=\"0.1\" step=\"0.1\" disabled={cart.length > 0}\n                          placeholder={cart.length > 0 ? \"يُستخدم الإجمالي من السلة\" : \"أدخل المبلغ...\"}\n                          value={customAmount} onChange={e => setCustomAmount(e.target.value)}\n                          className=\"w-full bg-slate-50 border border-slate-200 rounded-xl h-14 px-4 text-lg font-black text-slate-700 outline-none focus:border-orange-500 focus:ring-2 focus:ring-orange-100 transition-all disabled:opacity-50 disabled:bg-slate-100\" />\n                        <span className=\"absolute left-4 top-1/2 -translate-y-1/2 text-sm font-bold text-slate-400\">ر.س</span>\n                      </div>\n                      <button onClick={handleCheckout} disabled={!scannedStudent || (cart.length === 0 && !customAmount)}\n                        className=\"bg-orange-500 hover:bg-orange-600 disabled:opacity-50 disabled:hover:bg-orange-500 text-white px-8 rounded-xl font-black shadow-lg shadow-orange-500/30 transition-all flex items-center gap-2\">\n                        <CheckCircle2 size={20} /> تأكيد وخصم\n                      </button>\n                    </div>\n                  </div>\n\n                </div>\n              </div>\n            </motion.div>\n          )}\n\n          {/* TAB 2: INVENTORY */}\n          {activeTab === 'inventory' && (\n            <motion.div key=\"inv\" initial={{ opacity: 0, y: 10 }} animate={{ opacity: 1, y: 0 }} exit={{ opacity: 0 }} className=\"space-y-6\">\n              \n              {/* Add Item Form */}\n              <div className=\"bg-white rounded-[2rem] p-6 shadow-sm border border-slate-100\">\n                <h2 className=\"text-lg font-black text-slate-800 mb-6 flex items-center gap-2\">\n                  <Plus size={20} className=\"text-orange-500\" /> إضافة صنف جديد\n                </h2>\n                <form onSubmit={handleAddItem} className=\"flex flex-wrap md:flex-nowrap gap-4 items-end\">\n                  <div className=\"w-full md:w-[15%]\">\n                    <label className=\"block text-xs font-bold text-slate-500 mb-1.5 ml-1\">الرمز</label>\n                    <select value={newItem.icon} onChange={e => setNewItem({...newItem, icon: e.target.value})} className=\"w-full h-12 bg-slate-50 border border-slate-200 rounded-xl px-2 text-2xl outline-none focus:border-orange-400 text-center\">\n                      {EMOJIS.map(em => <option key={em} value={em}>{em}</option>)}\n                    </select>\n                  </div>\n                  <div className=\"w-full md:w-[25%]\">\n                    <label className=\"block text-xs font-bold text-slate-500 mb-1.5 ml-1\">اسم الصنف</label>\n                    <input type=\"text\" required placeholder=\"مثال: عصير تفاح\" value={newItem.name} onChange={e => setNewItem({...newItem, name: e.target.value})} className=\"w-full h-12 bg-slate-50 border border-slate-200 rounded-xl px-4 text-sm font-bold text-slate-700 outline-none focus:border-orange-400\" />\n                  </div>\n                  <div className=\"w-full md:w-[20%]\">\n                    <label className=\"block text-xs font-bold text-slate-500 mb-1.5 ml-1\">الفئة</label>\n                    <select value={newItem.category} onChange={e => setNewItem({...newItem, category: e.target.value})} className=\"w-full h-12 bg-slate-50 border border-slate-200 rounded-xl px-4 text-sm font-bold text-slate-700 outline-none focus:border-orange-400\">\n                      {CATEGORIES.map(cat => <option key={cat} value={cat}>{cat}</option>)}\n                    </select>\n                  </div>\n                  <div className=\"w-full md:w-[15%]\">\n                    <label className=\"block text-xs font-bold text-slate-500 mb-1.5 ml-1\">السعر</label>\n                    <input type=\"number\" required min=\"0.1\" step=\"0.1\" placeholder=\"0.0\" value={newItem.price} onChange={e => setNewItem({...newItem, price: e.target.value})} className=\"w-full h-12 bg-slate-50 border border-slate-200 rounded-xl px-4 text-sm font-bold text-slate-700 outline-none focus:border-orange-400\" />\n                  </div>\n                  <div className=\"w-full md:w-[15%]\">\n                    <label className=\"block text-xs font-bold text-slate-500 mb-1.5 ml-1\">الكمية الأولية</label>\n                    <input type=\"number\" required min=\"1\" placeholder=\"0\" value={newItem.quantity} onChange={e => setNewItem({...newItem, quantity: e.target.value})} className=\"w-full h-12 bg-slate-50 border border-slate-200 rounded-xl px-4 text-sm font-bold text-slate-700 outline-none focus:border-orange-400\" />\n                  </div>\n                  <div className=\"w-full md:w-[10%]\">\n                    <button type=\"submit\" className=\"w-full h-12 bg-slate-900 hover:bg-slate-800 text-white rounded-xl font-bold transition-colors flex justify-center items-center\">\n                      <Save size={18} />\n                    </button>\n                  </div>\n                </form>\n              </div>\n\n              {/* Menu Grid */}\n              <div className=\"bg-white rounded-[2rem] p-6 shadow-sm border border-slate-100 min-h-[400px]\">\n                <h2 className=\"text-lg font-black text-slate-800 mb-6 flex items-center gap-2\">\n                  <LayoutGrid size={20} className=\"text-orange-500\" /> المخزون الحالي ({menu.length})\n                </h2>\n                {menu.length === 0 ? (\n                  <div className=\"flex flex-col items-center justify-center py-20 opacity-50\">\n                    <Package size={64} className=\"text-slate-300 mb-4\" />\n                    <p className=\"text-lg font-bold text-slate-500\">لا يوجد أصناف في المخزون</p>\n                    <p className=\"text-sm font-bold text-slate-400 mt-2\">قم بإضافة أصناف جديدة من النموذج أعلاه</p>\n                  </div>\n                ) : (\n                  <div className=\"grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-2 lg:grid-cols-3 xl:grid-cols-4 gap-4\">\n                    {menu.map(item => (\n                      <div key={item.id} className=\"bg-slate-50 border border-slate-100 rounded-2xl p-4 flex flex-col relative group\">\n                        <button onClick={() => deleteItem(item.id)} className=\"absolute top-3 left-3 w-8 h-8 bg-white border border-slate-200 text-slate-400 hover:text-rose-500 hover:border-rose-200 hover:bg-rose-50 rounded-lg flex items-center justify-center transition-colors opacity-0 group-hover:opacity-100 shadow-sm z-10\">\n                          <Trash2 size={14} />\n                        </button>\n                        <div className=\"flex items-start gap-4 mb-4\">\n                          <div className=\"w-16 h-16 bg-white rounded-2xl shadow-sm flex items-center justify-center text-4xl border border-slate-100 shrink-0\">\n                            {item.icon}\n                          </div>\n                          <div>\n                            <p className=\"font-black text-slate-800 leading-tight mb-1\">{item.name}</p>\n                            <span className=\"inline-block bg-slate-200 text-slate-600 px-2 py-0.5 rounded-md text-[10px] font-bold mb-2\">{item.category}</span>\n                            <p className=\"text-sm font-black text-orange-500\">{item.price} ر.س</p>\n                          </div>\n                        </div>\n                        <div className=\"mt-auto bg-white rounded-xl border border-slate-200 p-1 flex items-center justify-between\">\n                          <button onClick={() => updateQuantity(item.id, -1)} className=\"w-8 h-8 rounded-lg bg-slate-50 hover:bg-slate-100 text-slate-600 font-bold flex items-center justify-center transition-colors\">-</button>\n                          <div className=\"flex flex-col items-center\">\n                            <span className={`text-sm font-black ${item.quantity < 5 ? 'text-rose-600' : 'text-slate-700'}`}>{item.quantity}</span>\n                            <span className=\"text-[9px] font-bold text-slate-400\">الكمية</span>\n                          </div>\n                          <button onClick={() => updateQuantity(item.id, 1)} className=\"w-8 h-8 rounded-lg bg-slate-50 hover:bg-slate-100 text-slate-600 font-bold flex items-center justify-center transition-colors\">+</button>\n                        </div>\n                      </div>\n                    ))}\n                  </div>\n                )}\n              </div>\n            </motion.div>\n          )}\n\n          {/* TAB 3: ORDERS */}\n          {activeTab === 'orders' && (\n            <motion.div key=\"orders\" initial={{ opacity: 0, y: 10 }} animate={{ opacity: 1, y: 0 }} exit={{ opacity: 0 }}>\n              <div className=\"bg-white rounded-[2rem] p-6 shadow-sm border border-slate-100 min-h-[500px]\">\n                <h2 className=\"text-lg font-black text-slate-800 mb-6 flex items-center gap-2\">\n                  <BellRing size={20} className=\"text-orange-500\" /> سجل الطلبات الشامل\n                </h2>\n                {orders.length === 0 ? (\n                  <div className=\"flex flex-col items-center justify-center py-32 opacity-50\">\n                    <Receipt size={64} className=\"text-slate-300 mb-4\" />\n                    <p className=\"text-lg font-bold text-slate-500\">لا توجد طلبات مسجلة</p>\n                  </div>\n                ) : (\n                  <div className=\"grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 lg:grid-cols-3 gap-4\">\n                    {orders.map(order => (\n                      <div key={order.id} className=\"bg-slate-50 border border-slate-100 rounded-2xl p-5 relative overflow-hidden group hover:border-orange-200 hover:shadow-md transition-all\">\n                        {order.source === 'pos' && (\n                          <div className=\"absolute top-0 right-0 bg-emerald-500 text-white text-[9px] font-black px-3 py-1 rounded-bl-xl shadow-sm z-10\">بيع مباشر</div>\n                        )}\n                        <div className=\"flex justify-between items-start mb-3 mt-1\">\n                          <div>\n                            <h3 className=\"font-black text-slate-800 text-sm flex items-center gap-1.5\"><div className=\"w-2 h-2 rounded-full bg-orange-500\"/> {order.studentName}</h3>\n                            <p className=\"text-[10px] font-mono text-slate-400 mt-1\">{order.studentId}</p>\n                          </div>\n                          <span className=\"text-[10px] font-bold text-slate-400 bg-white px-2 py-1 border border-slate-100 rounded-lg flex items-center gap-1\">\n                            <Clock size={10} /> {new Date(order.date).toLocaleTimeString('ar-EG', {hour: '2-digit', minute:'2-digit'})}\n                          </span>\n                        </div>\n                        <div className=\"bg-white rounded-xl p-3 border border-slate-100 mb-3 min-h-[60px]\">\n                          <p className=\"text-xs font-bold text-slate-600 leading-relaxed\">{order.items}</p>\n                        </div>\n                        <div className=\"flex items-center justify-between pt-2 border-t border-slate-200/50\">\n                          <span className=\"text-xs font-bold text-slate-500\">الإجمالي المخصوم</span>\n                          <span className=\"font-black text-orange-600 text-sm\">{order.total} ر.س</span>\n                        </div>\n                      </div>\n                    ))}\n                  </div>\n                )}\n              </div>\n            </motion.div>\n          )}\n\n        </AnimatePresence>\n      </main>\n    </div>\n  );\n};\n\nCafeteriaAdminDashboard.propTypes = {\n  onLogout: PropTypes.func.isRequired,\n};\n\nexport default CafeteriaAdminDashboard;","Description":"استبدال كود البوابة بالكامل لتطبيق التصميم الجديد والميزات المتكاملة وإزالة البيانات الوهمية.","Overwrite":true,"TargetFile":"c:\\al aws done\\moo_project\\src\\components\\CafeteriaAdminDashboard.jsx","toolAction":"Rewrite CafeteriaAdminDashboard","toolSummary":"Replace CafeteriaAdminDashboard component code"}}]}